==English==
===Etymology===
Coalitus Latin, mix together. Specifically used by U.S. President George Bush in 2003 to identify a small group of nations who joined the United States for the purpose of invading Iraq but were not traditional allies in the sense of NATO.

===Noun===
#  A temporary group, or union of organizations, usually formed for a particular advantage.
#  Any of a small group of nations offering troops to support the United States in exchange for compensation as opposed to an established alliance of nations who declare preemptive invasions illegal.

